{
  "title": "Slower Sociologies for the Sociology of the Future",
  "abstract": "In this article the use of old photograph techniques is considered as a way of ‘slowing sociology down’ in order to have more thoughtful and immersive engagement within the field. This is contrasted with contemporary methods and their emphasis on speed, efficiency and perfection.",
